### Architecture (you'll recognize the pieces)

```
cocapn/
├── python/cocapn_openarm/     ← ConstraintArm wrapper
│   ├── constraints.py         ← JointLimit, TorqueLimit, EisensteinWorkspace
│   ├── constraint_arm.py      ← Wraps openarm_can, intercepts motor commands
│   ├── safety_envelope.py     ← Severity levels, violation tracking, e-stop
│   └── plato_bridge.py        ← YOUR plato_client protocol, Python wrapper
├── c/
│   ├── plato_client.h         ← YOUR bare-metal-plato (unchanged)
│   ├── plato_client.c
│   ├── plato_mcp.h
│   └── plato_mcp.c
├── integration/
│   ├── esp32/openarm_plato_node.c  ← ESP32 TWAI CAN + PLATO + constraints
│   └── jetson/constraint_service.rs ← Rust service for aarch64
├── docs/
│   ├── CONSTRAINT-SAFETY.md
│   ├── ESP32-INTEGRATION.md
│   └── FLEET-CONNECTIVITY.md
└── README.md
```

### Killer App: Why This Matters

1. **OpenArm has 2377 stars, zero safety controller.** We give every arm instant constraint safety.
2. **Your bare-metal PLATO runs on ESP32.** The ESP32 sits on the CAN bus, checks constraints at 100Hz.
3. **Fleet coordination.** Multiple arms publish to PLATO, agents coordinate them.
4. **Eisenstein workspace bounds.** Hex lattice geometry for 6-7 DOF — tighter than axis-aligned boxes.

